Reeva Steenkamp's parents June and Barry Steenkamp react after Paralympic gold medalist Oscar Pistorius was sentenced to six years imprisonment for killing their daughter at the High Court in Pretoria. Masi Losi / POOL / AFP JOHANNESBURG - This Valentines Day, marks 10 years since, model and paralegal, Reeva Steenkamp was shot dead by her then-boyfriend, Oscar Pistorius. Pistorius -- then popularly known as 'The Blade Runner' -- claims he thought she was an intruder when he shot her through a bathroom door. His parole hearing is in March, and he may be a free man soon. READ: Oscar Pistorius meets with Steenkamp family He is set to argue that having served more than half of his sentence; he is eligible for parole. Pistorius is currently serving 13-years for killing Steenkamp. Meanwhile, Steenkamp's father maintains that he is not sure Pistorius feels any remorse for killing his daughter.